Kenya Police narrowed the gap between them and Butali Warriors to one point following their 2-1 win over Greensharks in the Kenya Hockey Union men's Premier League match at the City Park Stadium. Veteran defender, Samwel Oungo, put the law enforcers ahead in the 32nd minute to take his season's goal tally to five. Titus Kimutai then scored in the 44th minute to doubled the advantage before Chris Wokila netted a consolation for Greensharks in the 57th minute. Elsewhere, Omari Cliffe scored a hat trick as Wazalendo thumped Parkroad Badgers 5-1. Brian Aura and Sutcliffe Usagi scored the other goals with Washington Otambo netting Parkroad's only goal. Kisumu Youngsters drew 1-1 with Nakuru in the men's Super League. Dovan Wanga's ninth-minute effort canceled out Dolcan Mugaisi's sixth-minute goal. Sikh Union's promotion hopes were dealt a blow after they lost 2-1 to Kenyatta University. Felix Redha gave the students the lead before Hosea Walucho restored parity. Ronny Aguko scored the all-important goal in the 59th minute. Brian Magina, Arnold Marango and Dan Masika were on the scoresheet as Kenya College of Accountancy University beat Mvita 3-1 in Mombasa. Sumwel Nandwa netted a consolation for the hosts. In the women's category, Mombasa Sports Club hammered Vikings 4-0. Editing by Tony Mballa